@startuml syntax-repair
' lling-llang syntax-repair component diagram. A ParserBackend (foundation tier,
' blue) locates errors; the SyntaxRepairTransducer (correction & NLP tier, amber)
' proposes weighted edits over a token lattice and emits the least-cost repair.
' Palette: docs/diagrams/README.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #FFF59D
  BorderColor #F9A825
  FontColor #102027
}
skinparam interface {
  BackgroundColor #BBDEFB
  BorderColor #1565C0
}
skinparam ArrowColor #607D8B
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3

title <b>Syntax repair: ParserBackend ↔ SyntaxRepairTransducer</b>\n<size:11><i>parse → locate errors → weighted token edits → least-cost repair</i></size>

[source text] as SRC #ECEFF1

package "parsing (blue)" {
  interface "ParserBackend" as PB #BBDEFB
  component "tree-sitter /\nLALRPOP / pest /\nSimpleParserBackend" as IMPL #BBDEFB
  component "ParseResult<N>\n{ tree, errors:\nVec<ParserError> }" as PR #BBDEFB
}

package "repair (amber)" {
  component "tokenizer\n→ Vec<Token>" as TOK #B2DFDB
  component "SyntaxRepairTransducer<W>\n• rules: Vec<SyntaxRepairRule>\n• costs: SyntaxRepairCosts" as SRT
  component "find_repairs\n→ Vec<RepairCandidate>" as FIND
  component "select_non_overlapping\n(least-cost cover)" as SEL
}

[repaired text +\napplied repairs] as OUT #C8E6C9

SRC --> PB : parse(input)
PB ..> IMPL : implemented by
IMPL --> PR : tree + errors
SRC --> TOK : lex
PR --> SRT : error ranges /\nMISSING nodes
TOK --> SRT : Token stream
SRT --> FIND : apply weighted rules
FIND --> SEL : sort by cost <latex>\oplus = \min</latex>
SEL --> OUT : apply edits\n(reverse byte order)

note bottom of SRT
  Each rule carries a cost (a tropical weight under <b>W</b>):
  typo_fix 0.2 · missing_punctuation 0.3 · insert/delete/substitute 1.0.
  build_token_wfst(alphabet) lifts the rules into a VectorWfst<String, W>
  for composition with downstream transducers.
end note
@enduml
